Lagos State, through its Office of Establishments and Training, has begun  the training of  public officers One aspect of the training, with the theme: ‘Design and  Implementation of Key Performance Indicators in the State Public Service’, began yesterday at the State Secretariat Alausa, Ikeja.   Body to restore schools’ glory     House of Reps Aspirant seeks unity in Osun APC      Tinubu gets more support   It was attended by over 60 officers from the health sector, comprising the Health Service Commission, Public Health Board, Lagos State University Teaching Hospital and the Ministry of Health. The training was designed to ensure competencies in drawing up matrices to measure performance and achievement, and to equip officers with skills to prepare measures and indicators to be used to measure performance and achievement of set goals. Workshops are also being held in different locations in the state.